# Voice Debate AI Backend – Team Integration Guide

This backend powers the hec gen ai hackathon Voice-Based Debate AI application.

It handles:

* Audio upload
* Audio normalization
* Speech-to-text using Whisper
* AI debate response using Groq + Llama
* Scoring + feedback generation
* Text-to-speech response using ElevenLabs (with gTTS fallback if ElevenLabs fails)
* FastAPI API endpoints for frontend integration

# IMPORTANT: Read Before Editing Anything

Do NOT randomly change code structure.

This backend is already working and optimized.

Changing:

* prompt format
* file paths
* API response structure
* audio format
* environment variables

without coordination can break the full system.

Please read this file fully before touching code.

# Project Structure

backend/
│
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt
├── .env
│
├── input/
│   └── uploaded + normalized audio files
│
├── output/
│   └── generated AI voice response files
│
└── backup/
    └── old safe backup files


# Required Python Version

Use:

Python 3.11

Do NOT use Python 3.12 or 3.13 for this project.

Reason:
Some audio dependencies break on 3.12 and 3.13.

# Required Installation

Run in terminal:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

If issues happen:

```bash
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

# .env File Required

Inside it:

GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=your_elevenlabs_api_key_here

IMPORTANT:
Never push real API keys to GitHub.

Never delete `.env`.

Never rename variables.

# Run Backend

Start server using:

```bash
Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process
.\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
uvicorn app:app --reload
```

# Swagger UI:

It is used to test fastAPI

http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs


# Final Backend Response Format

Frontend must use EXACTLY this JSON structure:

```json
{
  "request_id": "",
  "status": "success",
  "transcript": "",
  "reply_text": "",
  "clarity": 0,
  "logic": 0,
  "evidence": 0,
  "persuasiveness": 0,
  "rebuttal_strength": 0,
  "score": 0,
  "feedback": "",
  "processing_time_seconds": 0,
  "response_audio_file": ""
}
```

Do NOT rename fields.

Do NOT remove fields.

Do NOT change data types.

Parser + frontend depend on this exact structure.

# Prompt Format (CRITICAL)

AI output MUST remain in this exact format:

Argument:
Clarity:
Logic:
Evidence:
Persuasiveness:
Rebuttal Strength:
Score:
Feedback:

If prompt structure changes:

```python
parse_gemini_output()
```

will break.

This is critical.

Do NOT change prompt labels.

# Audio Requirements (CRITICAL)

Frontend / Audio teammate must send:

.wav
mono channel
16kHz sample rate

Reason:
This keeps processing fast (~5.9s).

If random formats are sent:

* speed drops
* conversion slows
* failures increase

Avoid mp3/webm unless necessary.

# Current Performance

Average processing speed:

~5.9 seconds

Pipeline includes:

* transcription
* AI rebuttal
* scoring
* feedback
* TTS generation

This is optimized for hackathon demo.

# Fallback Safety

If:

* Groq fails
* ElevenLabs fails
* API temporary issue happens

System still falls back safely.

This is intentional.

Do NOT remove fallback logic.

Live demos must never fully fail.

# Safe Editing Rules

Before changing code:

## Always:

* make backup first
* test locally first
* tell team before major changes

## Never:

* replace full app.py blindly
* change API format without notice
* rename folders randomly
* hardcode API keys
* delete fallback logic
* change prompt labels casually

# Teammate Responsibilities

## Frontend

Uses:

* transcript
* reply_text
* score breakdown
* feedback
* response audio playback
* response time display

Recommended UI:

* mic button
* debate chat view
* score progress bars
* live scoreboard

## AI Logic

Responsible for:

* better prompts
* debate quality
* score realism
* stronger rebuttals

Must preserve parser format.

## Audio Processing

Responsible for:

* microphone quality
* correct file format
* noise reduction
* sending WAV properly

## Voice Output

Responsible for:

* ElevenLabs quality
* voice consistency
* fallback testing

# Emergency Backup Rule

Before hackathon final demo:

Create:

backup/app_final_working_backup.py

Never demo without backup.

Never trust live APIs without fallback.

